text: Valentin Zabransky (born February 2, 2007 in Vienna) is an Austrian football player. He plays as defender for the Austrian 2nd league team FC Liefering. == Career == Zabransky began his career at SV Essling. In September 2015 he moved to FC Stadlau. In December 2020, he moved to the youth team at FC Red Bull Salzburg. He also went through all age levels in the academy from the 2021/22 season on. For the 2024/25 season, Zabransky moved into the squad of FC Liefering. FC Liefering (German) He made his debut in the 2nd league in August 2024. He was in the starting line-up on the third matchday of that season against Schwarz-Wei√ü Bregenz. FC Salzburg Wiki ==International == Zabransky played for an Austrian youth national team for the first time in November 2021. In 2024 he took part in the European Championships with the U-17 team.
